 are discussed, such as the setting up of local archives and the training of local linguists. Numerous case studies illustrate different language shift environments with specific replacing factors, such as colonial and religious conquests, migrations and governmental language education. The book is of interest to students and scholars of linguistics with particular focus on endangered languages (and their documentation), typology, and sociolinguistics as well as to anthropologists and language activists.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aLanguage attrition. 4aBedrohte Sprache. 4aFeldforschung. 4aSpracherhaltung. 4aSprachwissenschaft /Sonstige Sprache.  aEndangered languages.  afieldwork.  alanguage documentation.  apreservation.1 aAdelaar, Willem F. H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBlench, Roger, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBradley, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrenzinger, Matthias, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrenzinger, Matthias, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aConnell, Bruce, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDriem, George, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEvans, Nicholas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGrinevald, Colette, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKazakevich, Olga, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKibrik, Aleksandr, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKrauss, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMoore, Denny, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary